<h3>Shared Principles and Properties</h3>
<div class="row">
    <div class="descriptive col-xs-12">
        <p>
            In addition the components above, there is every attempt to share functionality and principles across
            components. Here then are the main areas of reuse/shared principles:
        </p>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
        <ul>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-style'}}<code>style</code>{{/link-to}} - style consistency through style families</li>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-color'}}<code>color</code>{{/link-to}} - classy and specific colors</li>
            <li>
                {{#link-to 'shared-size'}}<code>size</code>{{/link-to}}
                {{#link-to 'shared-width-height'}}<code>width/height</code>{{/link-to}}
                 - standardized not <em>uniform</em> sizes</li>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-rules'}}<code>rules</code>{{/link-to}} - fire business logic; both built in rules and user defined</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
        <ul>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-textAlign'}}<code>textAlign</code>{{/link-to}} - text alignment w/in the control</li>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-status'}}<code>status</code>{{/link-to}} - visual indication of state</li>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-animation'}}<code>animation</code>{{/link-to}} - bring attention w/ animation</li>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-sound'}}<code>sound</code>{{/link-to}} - bring attention w/ sound effects</li>
            <li>{{#link-to 'shared-events'}}<code>events</code>{{/link-to}} - tbd</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    </div>
